1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we are going to delve deeper into how to personalize your 404 template.

2
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:09,600
A 404 page is also known as an error page or page not found.

3
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:14,240
It is the content a user sees when they try to reach a non-existent page on your website.

4
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:20,080
Most people who land on a default 404 page will probably leave your site immediately.

5
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:25,120
An unattractive or unengaging 404 page leads to poor user experience.

6
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:29,840
It increases the bounce rate of your site and will therefore negatively impact your SEO.

7
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:35,640
The quicker you can lead a visitor to the right place, the better.

8
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:38,880
As this example, if you create an engaging 404 page, you will hopefully ensure that visitors

9
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:44,120
stay and delve deeper into your site.

10
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:47,840
It is therefore important to create a custom 404 page and think of ways you can draw a

11
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:52,560
visitor's attention or even use humor.

12
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:55,440
I love this example from Pixar as it just makes you smile.

13
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:59,360
I also think Tendrik got it right by using an attention grabbing image, humor and a go-to

14
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:05,560
home page button.

15
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:08,640
To personalize or customize your 404 template, make your way to the Site Editor, open templates

16
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:15,400
and click on Page 404.

17
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,960
I am using the Twenty Twenty-Four default theme but every theme will set up this page differently.

18
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:24,560
Let's go ahead and modify this template to meet our requirements.

19
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:29,280
I am going to keep my header but delete the Group and Footer blocks.

20
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:35,240
Once deleted, I am going to add a Cover block and select an image from my media library.

21
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:50,240
Then I will add a Columns block with two equal columns.

22
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:57,160
And on the left hand side, I will add some text and write Keep calm and check your oxygen

23
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:05,760
levels.

24
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:10,160
Then I will change the size of the text to extra large.

25
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:20,640
And below this, I am going to add a Buttons block or a call to action

26
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:27,200
to take visitors to my home page, if they are accidentally land on a page not found.

27
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Then I will make the text bold and don't forget to add the home page link.

28
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,920
Then I will change the background color of the Buttons block to white and the text to

29
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:46,320
black.

30
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:49,280
We can also change the size of our Buttons block and in this case, I will go for medium.

31
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Once I have done that, I will select the Cover block and then toggle the Cover block to full

32
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:02,440
height.

33
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,760
And I will choose for the text to be displayed bottom left.

34
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:10,280
Then I will make my way to Styles and add some padding or some space around the content

35
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,360
of my block.

36
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:22,760
I am also going to change the overlay opacity of my cover block to 30% to make it slightly

37
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:28,960
lighter.

38
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:30,120
Then we can make our way to settings and for better mobile viewing, I will change the focal

39
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,040
point of the image.

40
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:41,240
And that was the last step.

41
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,480
So now we can go ahead and click Save and once we close my List View and sidebar settings,

42
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,280
we can see our personalized 404 template.

43
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,960
And then we can also check it out on mobile.

44
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:08,520
Another option when customizing or personalizing your 404 template is to use a pattern.

45
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:13,240
So in the second example, I am going to actually delete my header, Group block and footer to

46
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:18,440
start blank.

47
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,680
Then I will make my way to the WordPress.org site and go to the Patterns Directory.

48
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,560
And then I will search for 404 patterns.

49
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:35,280
But when you find a pattern you like, you can copy and paste it into your template.

50
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:44,560
Now you can modify it to meet your needs.

51
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,480
As you will notice in my updated version, I have added a home page link or call to action

52
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:55,320
as well as a footer with a search bar and links to my social media platforms.

53
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,240
All the best creating your own eye-catching and creative 404 page.

54
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:07,520
If your theme doesn't have a 404 template, you can check out the handbook to learn how

55
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:12,120
to add your own.

